title: Cesare
extract: Cesare Name Meaning. Italian: from the personal name Cesare, from the famous Roman family name Caesar. This was associated by folk etymology in classical times with Latin caesaries 'head of hair', but is probably of Etruscan origin, perhaps ultimately a cognate of Charles.
